description: Git commit and pull request conventions for alpinejs-toolkit
alwaysApply: true
---

## Git commit message

- Use **Conventional Commits**: `type(scope): description`.
- Valid types: `feat`, `fix`, `refactor`, `docs`, `test`, `chore`, `style`, `perf`, `build`, `ci`.
- Scope: package name without `alpine-` prefix (e.g. `theme`, `sidebar`, `overlay`).
- Keep the first line under ~72 characters; use the body for extra detail if needed.

## Before finishing any change

```bash
pnpm test
pnpm run lint
pnpm run typecheck   # when types changed
```
